  "theme": "Flood the table with green-and-white Voter tokens, fuel them with snacks and signature drives, then weaponize every group vote and recall into a referendum that strips the frontrunner's board.",
  "description": "Democracy, but with more shouting. Petunia Pitchfork has a clipboard, a bullhorn, and your signature whether you gave it or not — and she has HAD IT with the incumbent. This is a Selesnya (GW) grassroots recall movement: flood the table with green-and-white Voter tokens, fuel them with casseroles, lawn signs, and signature drives, then turn the Mayor's own elections against him as every group vote becomes a referendum she swings (her Voters tend to vote twice — Petunia checked, it's legal here). Nearly every payoff punishes whoever's out front, stripping the board of whichever player controls the most permanents, power, or votes. An acorn (Un-set) Commander deck with chaos kept deliberately LOW — almost-functional town-hall Magic thinning to a handful of chaos-5 fever-dreams — that tangles straight into the pod's votes, recounts, snacks, incumbents, dice, and coins. Color-identity and singleton rules are waived for acorn decks.",
